OL,3,CHow my father's fear triggered an
OL,4,Cinvestigation into last summer's riots
OL,6,FAs the interview rolls on I realise
OL,7,FDan's views are going to rile some and
OL,8,Frally others. This was an echo of
OL,9,Fothers in this area and the country,
OL,10,Fwho feel they've been ignored and left
OL,11,Fbehind.
OL,13,FAs part of the programme I also met
OL,14,FEric who has been waiting a staggering
OL,15,F15 years to get asylum in this country.
OL,17,FHe told me how he escaped the
OL,18,FDemocratic Republic of Congo as a
OL,19,Fteenager during a brutal civil war.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/16
