OL,3,CHow my father's fear triggered an
OL,4,Cinvestigation into last summer's riots
OL,6,FHe told me how he watched the angry
OL,7,Fmob shouting and trying to break in.
OL,8,FHe said that while hiding inside he
OL,9,Fencouraged all the others to pray to
OL,10,Ftheir God, because he was scared they
OL,11,Fwould all be killed.
OL,13,FFacing Eric and listening to his story
OL,14,FI'm reminded that in this long running
OL,15,Fargument about immigration, many have
OL,16,Fforgotten their humanity and the fact
OL,17,Fthat everyone has a right to feel
OL,18,Fsafe. Something that was far from the
OL,19,Fminds of those storming these hotels.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G14/16
